<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Simpl Design</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
    <style>
        .card {
            background-color: rgba(224, 224, 224, 0.8);
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        
        .card-body {
            padding: 20px;
        }
        
        .card-title {
            color: #333;
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        
        .card-text {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <%- include('partials/navbar.ejs') %>
    </header>
    
    <div class="container mt-4">
        <h1>Explore Different Interior Design Styles</h1>
        
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Color Palette:</strong> Note the predominant colors used in the style. This includes wall colors, furniture, and accent pieces.</li>
            <li><strong>Furniture and Layout:</strong> Pay attention to the types of furniture used and their arrangement. Note if the furniture is minimalist, ornate, modern, etc.</li>
            <li><strong>Materials and Textures:</strong> Identify the materials used for flooring, walls, and furniture. Note textures such as smooth, rough, glossy, matte, etc.</li>
            <li><strong>Patterns and Prints:</strong> Look for recurring patterns or prints used in textiles, wallpapers, or decorative elements.</li>
            <li><strong>Lighting:</strong> Observe the type and placement of lighting fixtures. Note if the style favors natural light, ambient lighting, or dramatic lighting effects.</li>
            <li><strong>Overall Atmosphere:</strong> Describe the overall atmosphere or mood created by the style. Note if it feels cozy, formal, relaxed, etc.</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>Don't worry if you find it challenging to understandâ€”let our interior designers assist you during your first consultation.</p>

        <% for(let i = 0; i < designs.length; i++) { %>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title"><%= designs[i].style %></h5>
                    <p class="card-text">
                        <h4><%= designs[i].description %></h4>
                        <br>
                        <strong>Color Scheme:</strong> <%= designs[i].color_scheme %>
                        <br>
                        <strong>Material and Texture:</strong> <%= designs[i].material %>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <img src="images/<%= designs[i].image %>" class="card-img-bottom img-fluid" alt="<%= designs[i].style %> image">
            </div>
            <br>
        <% } %>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
